item.title: Help with script
item.dc:creator: @solemn_wishes solemn wishes
item.description:
@solemn_wishes wrote:

You specified a ‘Begin’ in the wrong place, you dont need to specify the beginning of a script like you did.

You put the ‘Var’ in the wrong place in your ‘movetotrees’ procedures,. should be before the begin.

you used two ends; when you only needed one.

your using ‘findcolor’ and ‘MouseC’. Id suggest doing some research into the include you are using before scripting!

I made your script work, but i do not my any means suggest using this for anything but a leraning resource

[code]program sorenslicer;
{.include SRL/SRL.scar}

Procedure MoveToTrees;
Var X, Y : Integer;
Begin

FindColor(x,y, 10859443, 587, 105, 597, 112);
MMouse(x,y,5,5)

End;

Begin;
SetupSRL;
MoveToTrees;
End.[/code]
